@startuml
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
'
' Current-side use cases for /mdd-deploy, derived from the implemented
' code: templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL (steps 1-11) + .mdd/docs/deploy-
' profile.md, materialized into .claude/.codex/skills/mdd-deploy/SKILL.md
' by `mdd init`. Standalone utility, a sibling of /mdd-render, NOT routed
' into any gate.
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0016): the implemented skill is now ADAPTIVE — two new
' operator-facing gates (deployment purpose, access-completeness) join the
' dialect gate, and the landmine pause is generalized to any ungrounded
' fact. Both new gates SURFACE options; they never bake in an answer.
'
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL: /mdd-deploy produces a deployment diagram + secure-by-default generated IaC in the operator-CONFIRMED dialect + a STOP-gated runbook for azure-container-apps, pausing with a blocking clarification on ambiguity and on any GENERALIZED landmine — any choice whose correctness depends on a fact not grounded in the inputs it read (app-config, purpose, and access-path axes; steps 3/5/6) — surfacing the gap instead of jumping to a solution. Executes no deploy command.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "Implemented: templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Additive, non-gating.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT, "Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL step 4 (+ deploy-profile.md): the dialect is exactly one of bicep or terraform per run; the skill resolves it and BLOCKS for explicit operator confirmation before writing ANY deploy artifact. No silent default; Terraform enforces the same invariants + secure-by-default posture as Bicep, differing only in structure.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE, "Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL step 5 (+ deploy-profile.md 'Deployment purpose — operator-confirmed'): before any purpose-driven default, the skill establishes dev/staging/prod and BLOCKS for explicit operator confirmation — no silent default, never assumes prod- or dev-grade. The confirmed purpose drives DB tier/redundancy, backup retention and the RECOMMENDED network/doorway posture; the skill surfaces the options for the operator to confirm and preserves secure-by-default. Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-PURPOSE / -SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK, "Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL step 6 (+ deploy-profile.md 'Access-completeness'): before writing artifacts, the skill accounts for who READS and who WRITES every secured store (Key Vault, DB, ACR, remote state), each with an identity and a network path the posture admits. A store read-but-never-written, or a writer with no admitted path, is SURFACED as a blocking question with the connectivity options framed by purpose; the operator chooses. Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-ACCESS-COMPLETE / -SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.")
title /mdd-deploy deployment guidance — use cases (current)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "Guide an Azure Container Apps\ndeployment via a diagram,\nrunbook, and generated IaC" as Guide
  usecase "Choose & CONFIRM the IaC dialect\n(Bicep XOR Terraform) before any\nartifact is written — no silent default" as Dialect
  usecase "Confirm the deployment PURPOSE\n(dev/staging/prod) before any\npurpose-driven default — no silent default" as Purpose
  usecase "Account for who READS and WRITES\nevery secured store (identity + admitted\npath) before emitting — surface holes" as AccessCheck
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Dialect
Op --> Purpose
Op --> AccessCheck
Op --> Inspect

Guide ..> Dialect : <<include>>
Guide ..> Purpose : <<include>>
Guide ..> AccessCheck : <<include>>
Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>

note bottom of Guide
  Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL:
  v1 supports only azure-container-apps. Reads MDD
  models + the target repo read-only. PAUSES with a
  BLOCKING clarification (step 3) on ambiguity OR a
  GENERALIZED go-live landmine — any choice whose
  correctness depends on a fact NOT grounded in the
  inputs (app-config / purpose / access-path axes) —
  surfacing the gap, never a buried runbook STOP note.
  Writes diagram + runbook + SECURE-BY-DEFAULT IaC in
  the confirmed dialect, then STOPS. Never runs
  az/docker/terraform/brew.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Dialect
  Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL step 4.
  Mandatory <<include>>: guidance cannot proceed until
  the dialect is explicitly confirmed. One per run
  (Bicep XOR Terraform). FULL PARITY; no silent default.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Purpose
  Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL step 5.
  Mandatory <<include>>: no purpose-driven default is
  generated until dev/staging/prod is confirmed. No
  silent default; never assume prod- or dev-grade.
  RECOMMENDS sizing/posture; operator confirms;
  secure-by-default preserved. Constrained by
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-PURPOSE / -SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of AccessCheck
  Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL step 6.
  Mandatory <<include>>: before emitting, every secured
  store must have a named READER and WRITER, each with
  an admitted network path. A read-but-never-written
  store, or a writer with no admitted path, is SURFACED
  as a blocking question — not shipped. Constrained by
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-ACCESS-COMPLETE / -SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Inspect
  Not a gate. /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the
  /mdd-cycle parity loop never read .mdd/deploy/.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT.
end note
@enduml
